The paper introduces a new algorithm for Co-Clustering, which is a problem in machine learning and data mining. The algorithm is scalable, hyperparameter-free, and can handle massive cross-domain datasets. These characteristics suggest that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category since the paper focuses on a new algorithm for Co-Clustering, which is a machine learning problem. The other categories are also possible since the paper deals with large datasets, optimization, and graph-based representations, which are relevant to these sub-fields.
